PSG Group Ltd. (PSG)  will buy CA
Enterprises, a Botswana-based consumer goods distributor, for
300 million rand ($39 million), the  Financial Mail  reported.  The investment holding company is looking for other
acquisitions in Africa, the Johannesburg-based weekly magazine
said, citing Chief Executive Officer Piet Mouton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
